---
sunspot: ! "Usage: sunspot-solr <command> <options> -- <application options>\n\n*
  where <command> is one of:\n  start         start an instance of the application\n
  \ stop          stop all instances of the application\n  restart       stop all
  instances and restart them afterwards\n  run           start the application and
  stay on top\n  zap           set the application to a stopped state\n\n* and where
  <options> may contain several of the following:\n\n    -t, --ontop                      Stay
  on top (does not daemonize)\n    -f, --force                      Force operation\nCommon
  options:\n    -h, --help                       Show this message\n        --version
  \                   Show version\n\nUsage: sunspot-solr start [options]\n    -p,
  --port=PORT                  Port on which to run Solr (default 8983)\n    -d, --data-directory=DIRECTORY
  \  Solr data directory\n    -s, --solr-home=HOME             Solr home directory
  (should contain conf/ directory)\n        --pid-dir=PID_DIR            Directory
  for pid files\n    -l, --log-level=LOG_LEVEL        Solr logging level\n        --log-file=LOG_FILE
  \         Path to Solr log file\n        --max-memory=MEMORY          Specify the
  maximum size of the memory allocation pool\n        --min-memory=MEMORY          Specify
  the initial size of the memory allocation pool"
